<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Work-and-Twist" class="currentChild" href="Work-and-Twist">Work-and-Twist</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Prepress" href="Prepress">prepress</a> and printing, an <a title="Imposition" href="Imposition">imposition</a> or layout in which one negative <a title="Flat" href="Flat">flat</a> is used to make two images on a plate. After the negative has produced one image on the plate, the flat is rotated 180º and a second exposure made. Work-and-twist layouts are used in <a title="Two-Up" href="Two-Up">two-up</a> printing. See also <a title="Work-and-Tumble" href="Work-and-Tumble">Work-and-Tumble</a> and <a title="Work-and-Turn" href="Work-and-Turn">Work-and-Turn</a>. 
</p>
<div style="clear: both;"></div></div>


